https://developer.apple.com/devcenter/mac/index.action#downloads

Recent version of command_line_tools_for_os_x_mavericks (250mb installed)

HomeBrew script will prompt to install developer tools if not already present

Install Homebrew using OS X default ruby

ruby -e "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/master/install)"

http://caskroom.io

brew install caskroom/cask/brew-cask

brew cask install google-chrome

Installs in Users home by default

open ~/Applications/"Google Chrome.app"

brew cask install dropbox

ZSH 
brew install zsh
sudo -e /etc/shells

Add line
/usr/local/bin/zsh
chsh -s /usr/local/bin/zsh
prompted to create .zshrc


